## Part 3: Scalability Architecture

### Current (Demo)
```
25 trucks → Mosquitto → Python → Flask (single server)
```
**Bottleneck:** Single Flask instance, in-memory state, no persistence.

### Production (10,000+ trucks)
```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                    IoT Sensors (100K+ trucks)                │
│            BLE temp loggers → Truck Gateway (4G/LTE)         │
└──────────────────────────┬──────────────────────────────────┘
                           │ MQTT/AMQP
                           ▼
┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                AWS IoT Core / EMQX Cluster                   │
│          (Managed MQTT broker, auto-scales to millions)      │
└──────────────┬───────────────────────────┬───────────────────┘
               │                           │
               ▼                           ▼
┌──────────────────────────┐  ┌────────────────────────────────┐
│     Apache Kafka          │  │      Pathway (Distributed)     │
│  (Event stream buffer,    │  │   - MQTT bridge connector      │
│   replay, durability)     │  │   - Risk scoring pipeline      │
│   3 brokers, repl. = 3    │  │   - RAG document store         │
└──────────┬───────────────┘  │   - Metrics aggregation        │
           │                   └──────────┬─────────────────────┘
           ▼                              │
┌──────────────────────────┐              ▼
│    TimescaleDB            │  ┌────────────────────────────────┐
│  (Time-series storage,    │  │   Redis Cluster                │
│   compress 10:1)          │  │   (Real-time state cache,      │
│   Partitioned by month    │  │    pub/sub for dashboard SSE)  │
└──────────────────────────┘  └──────────┬─────────────────────┘
                                          │
                                          ▼
                              ┌────────────────────────────────┐
                              │   React/Next.js Dashboard       │
                              │   (CDN-served, WebSocket,       │
                              │    multi-tenant, mobile-first)  │
                              └────────────────────────────────┘
                              ┌────────────────────────────────┐
                              │   Kubernetes (EKS)              │
                              │   Auto-scaling, health checks,  │
                              │   blue-green deployments        │
                              └────────────────────────────────┘
```

### Scaling Numbers

| Component | Demo | Production |
|-----------|------|------------|
| Trucks | 25 | 100,000+ |
| Messages/sec | ~50 | 500,000+ |
| MQTT Broker | Mosquitto (single) | EMQX Cluster / AWS IoT Core |
| Database | In-memory dict | TimescaleDB (compressed) |
| Cache | None | Redis Cluster |
| Dashboard | Flask (single) | React + CDN + WebSocket |
| Deployment | Docker Compose | Kubernetes (EKS) |
| Storage | None | 1TB/month compressed |

