## Part 6: What to Say When Judges Ask

**"Will this work at scale?"**
> "Our architecture is designed for horizontal scaling. MQTT handles millions of connections, Kafka buffers events for durability, Pathway processes streams in real-time, and TimescaleDB compresses time-series data 10:1. We can scale from 25 to 100,000 trucks by adding nodes, not rewriting code."

**"What's your business model?"**
> "SaaS with tiered pricing — ₹25K to ₹5L/month based on fleet size. For every ₹1 customers spend on LiveCold, they save ₹25 in prevented spoilage. Our gross margin is 80%+ because it's pure software."

**"What's your moat?"**
> "Three things: (1) Our AI decision engine doesn't just alert — it recommends cost-optimal actions with exact ₹ savings. (2) Live SOP compliance using Pathway's real-time document processing — competitors don't have this. (3) India-specific: our risk model, hub database, and pricing are built for Indian cold chain realities."

**"What are the biggest risks?"**
> "Sensor reliability (we solve with anomaly filtering and multi-sensor redundancy), network gaps in rural India (we solve with edge computing), and driver adoption (we solve with WhatsApp/SMS alerts in regional languages)."
